[1]
Date: Fri, 05 Sep 1997 10:31:28 -0600
From: Mark Larocco <ZMTL02@SLEH.COM>
The recovery of penicillin-resistant Streptococcus pneumoniae from pediatric
patients with chronic otitis media has been well-described in the literature.
A few citations:
1. MMWR, 1994;43:23-6, 31
2. Antimicrob. Agents Chemotherap., 1992, 36:1703-1707
3. Antimicrob. Agents Chemotherap., 1995, 39:271-272
In my own laboratory the percentage of pneumococcal clinical isolates that
show high level resistance to penicillin (MIC >2 ug/ml) is 15%, many of these
isolates have been recovered from middle ear effusions from children.
---
Mark LaRocco, Ph.D.
Director of Clinical Microbiology
St. Luke's Episcopal Hospital
Houston, Texas USA
