Date: Fri, 05 Sep 1997 07:52:07 +0000
From: FRANK MYERS III <FRANKM@MERCYSD.COM>
This is clearly not the first [resistant] _Streptococcus pneumoniae_
reported. I refer subscribers to: Centers for Disease Control. Drug
Resistant Streptococcus Pneumoniae- Kentucky and Tennessee, 1993. MMWR
1994;43:23-25 in which 361 children with otitis media were described. Of
those 110 were positive for pneumococci of those 32 had penicillin resistance
(>2.0 mcg/ml).
---
Frank Myers, M.A.
